Check out the NYE menu at @june.nashville! Each year we create somewhere around 160 different menu items. Each NYE we will compile our greatest hits of the year and serve them one more time. These creations only stick around for a 6 week menu cycle and when they are gone they are gone. Well, unless they make the NYE Greatest Hits Menu. This will be so fun! Link in bio. Also let us know if your favorite dish didn’t make it, Happy Holidaze!

This is my favorite menu we have done at @june.nashville, maybe my fave of all time. 

Since we opened in mid July we have served over 80 different creations. Every 6 weeks or so we change the menu entirely. We challenge ourselves tirelessly to never stop creating, curiously trying to discover something new, day in and day out. 

The last service for this menu and these dishes is Friday December 30th. Try not to miss this one!

We are  gonna have a bunch of stuff for the hot grab and go case, gas station style. The burrito is fun it has @giffordsbacon, cheesy egg custard, more cheddar, waffle hash brown, Valentina-sorghum sauce & sour cream. Grab a sandwich and a burrito! Happy New Year!🎆🎊🎈

A very fun MENU EXPANSION is debuting at @thecontinentalnashville tonight! Pictured is the one of the most insanely ridiculous classics, “Tournedos Rossini”. The most outrageously fun thing I’ve eaten in a long long time. Come see us, @trey_tench and the team have added 15-20 new offerings!

Debuted menu 5 tonight at @june.nashville. This menu will only be offered for 17 more services after tonight. Changing the menu 8 times a year is quite hectic but I enjoy it because it pushes us to never stop creating, thinking, wandering or discovering. Next week we start sketching out the late winter menu that will debut in February. The idea came from wanting to focus on splitting the seasons in two, investigating the early part of the season and then the latter part of the season.  So far it’s been wild and wonderful. Thank y’all so much for the support and thank you to my amazing team for the passion and grit it takes to pull this craziness off and have fun at the same time. 🙏

The team at @thecontinentalnashville has been working hard to refine and expand our dining experience. It is so much fun, we hope to see you soon for dinner or brunch!

Mesmerizing Herb oil process by @elliotsil at @thelabataudrey . A solvent is used to extract as much flavor, pigment and aroma as possible, without heat involved. The result is the definition of vibrant and fresh. This can’t be achieved when the herb is blanched or cooked by the heat of the blender.

I am so excited about this new Dinner Series at @audreynashville. “FEAST OF FRIENDS” is inspired by sharing ideas, flavors, and traditions with people we admire and find hugely inspiring. 
 

We learn so much when people come to visit us. We learn so much more than cooking and hospitality, we get to see a new perspective on running restaurants and striving for excellence. The first one in the books was with @chefjameskent and it was one of the funniest nights I’ve ever had in a kitchen. Having his team here sharing their perspective makes our restaurants better instantly. And that is exactly what we are all trying to do, make the best experience for our guests and team.

The Feast is a family style tasting menu experience that allows us to collab on dishes and present our dishes side by side as well.

I randomly said hello to a couple who had a @leicacamerausa at @frankiesnashville several weeks ago. Within a few short moments their passion for extraordinary tea and coffee and their curiosity  for the science of extraction made it pretty darn obvious that we needed to do something fun together. The following talk about doing a pop up revealed even more of their theories around the future of beverage hospitality and the constant pursuit of new methods and technologies to show the ultimate respect to everyone involved in the process.  They are going to set up shop during the day starting October 10th and will be open Tuesday through Saturday from 8-2pm. I hope they stick around forever, everything I have tasted has changed my perception of coffee altogether and I can’t wait for them to share with you what I’ve been lucky enough to taste and hear about. Their vision for a coffee and tea  bar that feels like an omakase experience feels right at home alongside the way we think about our respective crafts and the new experience at @barcontinentalhifi. Please help me welcome them to Nashville properly and give them a follow. Hope to see you soon, Prepare to have your minds blown.

When I tasted Jimmy Red for the first time 15 years ago all I could think about was how to get this extraordinary flavor in front of as many people as possible. As chefs, we have the opportunity in our restaurants to expose people to new flavors every day, but how do we get these flavors in front of even more people each day? Supply and demand is a real thing, the more people that taste these flavors, the more people will hopefully want them again and that requires us to plant more, which helps our farmers. 

In my opinion, the answer to this question is retail. Five years ago we met with @wholefoods and pitched this idea. Some things have happened in the world since then that certainly slowed this dream down a little, but we stuck with it. 

Fast forward to my trip to @wholefoods today to shop for Thanksgiving. Walking past these on the aisle is one of the most fulfilling things I’ve experienced. 
The memory of Nava seeing my photo on the back of the bag and screaming Poppa! will bring a smile to my face for many many years to come. 

Thank you so much to @ansonmills, @marshhenmill, my biz partner, my team, @samuel.jett, @dustjust23, @kstein06 and everyone at @wholefoods for all the work and resources to allow us to have a much bigger stage for our beloved heirloom corn. These are available in the South only for now. Appreciate the support @southbyseanbrock
